    <item>
      <title>Sōzu 1.0.2 is available and deployed</title>
      <link>https://lafillepassympa.com/developers/changelog/2024-06-07-sozu-1.0.2/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 07 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://lafillepassympa.com/developers/changelog/2024-06-07-sozu-1.0.2/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;After the availability of Sōzu 1.0 in release candidate and an extensive testing phase, we&amp;rsquo;ve identified and fixed some bugs. Over the last few days, we&amp;rsquo;ve been deploying version 1.0.2 across all our regions, and it&amp;rsquo;s now fully used in production. This new branch brings a lot of improvements, security and new features to our open source Rust based reverse proxy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The communication between processes is more efficient thanks to &lt;a href=&#34;https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protocol_Buffers&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;ProtoBuf&lt;/a&gt;, which is now widely used in Sōzu. We&amp;rsquo;ve improved the performance through &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/rustls/rustls/pull/1774&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;our contribution to Rustls&lt;/a&gt;, added colors to logs. Process configuration is 50% faster, certificates renewal has been optimized, and their resolution is now significantly more responsive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&amp;rsquo;ve also fixed a bug affecting socket timeouts on frontends, ensuring better handling of requests.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.sozu.io&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;New Sōzu website&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn more about &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/sozu-proxy/sozu/releases&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Sōzu new releases&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;hx-inline-block hx-align-text-bottom icon&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1em fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; viewBox=&#34;3 3 18 18&#34;&gt;
